Fluorescence of CDs significantly quenched with increase in atorvastatin concentration. As shown in Fig. 5
                        , there are two linear ranges. Stern-Volmer equations are (F0/F = 0.3612CAtorvastatin (μM) +1.0222; R2 = 0.9985; LDR = 0.025–1 μM) and (F0/F = 0.0841CAtorvastatin (μM) +1.0854; R2 = 0.9938; LDR = 5–50 μM). Limit of detection (LOD) was 0.8 nM under the optimal experimental conditions based on LOD = 3 s/m and slop of the first calibration range. Performance of the mentioned method is also compared with other analytical methods (Table 1
                        ). The proposed method has excellent detection limit and is rapid, simple, and low cost.
